Benchmarks for KBC and LM-as-KB cover facts for all kinds of entities, but tend to focus on prominent ones with frequent mentions. Likewise, benchmarks for 
relation extraction (RE) from text, most notably TACRED [zhang2017position], DocRED [yao2019docred] and LAMA [petroni2019language]
do not reflect the difficulty of coping with long-tail entities and the amplified issue of surface-name ambiguity (see Table (ref).
Therefore, we developed a new dataset with
emphasis on the long-tail challenge,
called MALT (for 
``Multi-token, Ambiguous, Long-Tailed facts'').